<h1 style="color:Tomato;"><center>HTML</center></h1>
<b> HTML (HyperText Markup Language) </b><br/>
<i>HTML (HyperText Markup Language)</i><br/>
<u>HTML (HyperText Markup Language)</u><br/>

<p>The HyperText Markup Language, or HTML is the standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web browser. 
It can be assisted by technologies such as Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) and scripting languages such as JavaScript.</p>
 
<p><b>The major points of HTML are given below:</b> <br> 1) HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language.<br>
2) HTML is used to create web pages and web applications. <br>3) HTML is widely used language on the web.
<br> 4) We can create a static website by HTML only.<br>5) Technically, HTML is a Markup language rather than a programming language.</p>

<p> <font size="4" face="Bahnschrift Condensed">  1) An HTML element starts with a start tag / opening tag.<br>
    2) An HTML element ends with an end tag / closing tag. </font> </p>

